The paper deals with image classification models and their pathologies, specifically focusing on convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses strategies to improve the accuracy of the models, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the statistical patterns of the image classification benchmark, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the potential fragility of the models in real-world deployment, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
